    "e4b72051-2ba0-485d-a962-921fb0e7ffef": {
      "type": "content-tab",
      "blocks": {
        "dee15880-9763-4e22-ae54-275fef2d1994": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "shopify://shop_images/icones_-01.png",
            "text": "Start by giving them a gentle cleaning with a brush or cloth to get rid of any excess dirt or grime.",
            "tab_selection": "1"
          }
        },
        "bb5f0e68-e09a-486d-bdd4-4916642228c0": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "shopify://shop_images/icones_-02.png",
            "text": "Begin by removing any loose dirt or debris from the surface of the shoes using a soft-bristled brush or a dry cloth. Brush gently in a back-and-forth motion to lift the dirt out of the fibers of the material.",
            "tab_selection": "2"
          }
        },
        "a35f0fd9-8d5a-43ba-93d7-7d5b46209a66": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "shopify://shop_images/icones_-02.png",
            "text": "Start by using a soft-bristled brush to gently brush away any dirt or debris on the surface of the velvet. Avoid using a stiff brush or rubbing the material too hard, as this can damage the delicate fibers of the velvet.",
            "tab_selection": "3"
          }
        },
        "heading_CbUHU3": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "shopify://shop_images/icones_-01.png",
            "text": "Start by wiping the shoes with a soft, damp cloth to remove any surface dirt or debris. This simple step can often refresh the appearance of the shoes.",
            "tab_selection": "4"
          }
        },
        "heading_cAtgiP": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "shopify://shop_images/icones_-01.png",
            "text": "Start by giving them a gentle clean using a soft brush or dry cloth to remove any surface dirt or dust.",
            "tab_selection": "5"
          }
        },
        "10c677b4-1538-4ec7-abd2-7955d64c31b4": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "shopify://shop_images/icones_-04.png",
            "text": "Then, soak the fabric in naturally soapy water (no need to dunk the whole shoe in there, folks).",
            "tab_selection": "1"
          }
        },
        "f4cb5203-1c7d-4c26-85b9-723aa7b491ee": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "shopify://shop_images/icones_-04.png",
            "text": "If there are any stubborn stains on the shoes or item, mix a small amount of mild detergent with warm water to create a gentle cleaning solution. Dip a clean cloth into the solution, then wring it out so it's damp but not soaking wet. Gently rub the affected area with the cloth, being careful not to saturate the material with too much liquid.",
            "tab_selection": "2"
          }
        },
        "def71dfa-9784-4315-804a-82f37526ce13": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "shopify://shop_images/icones_-04.png",
            "text": "If there are any stubborn stains on the shoes, mix some detergent for delicate textilers with some water and dab the affected area softly with a clean cloth, taking care not to saturate the velvet with too much liquid. Allow the shoes to air dry after cleaning.",
            "tab_selection": "3"
          }
        },
        "heading_Yn8iUg": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "shopify://shop_images/icones_-04.png",
            "text": "If you see bigger stains, you can use a gentle cleanser specifically formulated for vegan leather. Apply a small amount of the cleanser to a soft cloth and gently rub it onto the shoes in circular motions. Wipe off any excess cleanser with a clean, damp cloth and avoid soaking vegan leather shoes in water, as it can damage the material. ",
            "tab_selection": "4"
          }
        },
        "heading_jTkgNr": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "shopify://shop_images/icones_-04.png",
            "text": "Once brushed off, soak a clean cloth or brush in a bowl of naturally soapy water (nothing too harsh). Simply focus on dunking the towel fabric, giving it a good scrub where needed. The fabric is very absorbent, so avoid soaking the whole shoe — it holds water for a long time and may shrink or warp when drying.Pay special attention to any areas with visible stains or heavier wear.",
            "tab_selection": "5"
          }
        },
        "1c376da2-8321-46ba-b11e-622dd946cf08": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "shopify://shop_images/icones_-02.png",
            "text": "Use a brush to scrub away any stubborn stains or dirt, being extra thorough in those problem areas.",
            "tab_selection": "1"
          }
        },
        "f8c652c2-cf53-4372-9603-12002ef992ba": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "shopify://shop_images/icones_-02.png",
            "text": "For tougher stains, you can also use a synthetic suede eraser or a white pencil eraser to gently rub the affected area. This can help to lift the stain without damaging the material.",
            "tab_selection": "2"
          }
        },
        "ff091b8f-728e-412e-8528-4f98a90847aa": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "shopify://shop_images/icones_-02.png",
            "text": "For general maintenance and upkeep, store your velvet shoes in a dry, cool place, away from direct sunlight. You can also use a soft-bristled brush to gently fluff the velvet nap from time to time.",
            "tab_selection": "3"
          }
        },
        "0d849b65-54dc-4438-a229-f6a20f8cf633": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "shopify://shop_images/icones_-03.png",
            "text": "Rinse with clean water (remember, no soaking necessary) and make sure to get rid of all soap residue.",
            "tab_selection": "1"
          }
        },
        "heading_GNX4jR": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "shopify://shop_images/icones_-03.png",
            "text": "Then rinse gently with clean water, just enough to remove the soap. Be sure all soapy residue is gone.",
            "tab_selection": "5"
          }
        },
        "0dc22562-1b83-42ed-86cf-4173e9a1290c": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "shopify://shop_images/icones_-05.png",
            "text": "Once you've finished cleaning the shoes, allow them to air dry away from direct heat or sunlight. Avoid using a hair dryer or other heat source to dry the shoes, as this can cause the material to warp or shrink.",
            "tab_selection": "2"
          }
        },
        "01b65076-321e-47b7-a2a9-c755ec00012d": {
          "type": "heading",
          "disabled": true,
          "settings": {
            "icon": "shopify://shop_images/icones_-03.png",
            "text": "Rinse with clean water (remember, no soaking necessary) and make sure to get rid of all soap residue.",
            "tab_selection": "3"
          }
        },
        "f75b1609-1930-4a3a-bfe0-603aa41d52fc": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "shopify://shop_images/icones_-05.png",
            "text": "Finally, pop them in a cool, dry place out of direct sunlight or heat sources to avoid any wrinkling or color loss.",
            "tab_selection": "1"
          }
        },
        "heading_nYmKJg": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "shopify://shop_images/icones_-05.png",
            "text": "After cleaning, allow the shoes to air dry naturally in a well-ventilated area away from direct heat sources or sunlight. Stuff the shoes with paper towels or a dry cloth to help them maintain their shape as they dry.",
            "tab_selection": "4"
          }
        },
        "heading_GmPH47": {
          "type": "heading",
          "settings": {
            "icon": "shopify://shop_images/icones_-05.png",
            "text": "Place your shoes in a cool, dry spot, away from any direct sunlight or heat waves.",
            "tab_selection": "5"
          }
        },
        "65af5542-fcd4-46eb-af3c-38002732e1f8": {
          "type": "heading",
          "disabled": true,
          "settings": {
            "icon": "shopify://shop_images/Ilustracion_5.png",
            "text": "Finally, pop them in a cool, dry place out of direct sunlight or heat sources to avoid any wrinkling or color loss.",
            "tab_selection": "2"
          }
        },
        "ad53dfb3-19df-474f-b3a0-1e9638a819ca": {
          "type": "heading",
          "disabled": true,
          "settings": {
            "icon": "shopify://shop_images/Ilustracion_5.png",
            "text": "Finally, pop them in a cool, dry place out of direct sunlight or heat sources to avoid any wrinkling or color loss.",
            "tab_selection": "3"
          }
        },
