      "settings": {
        "css_class": "product-care--content-tab",
        "tab_1": "Cotton / polyester",
        "tab_2": "Synthetic Suede",
        "tab_3": "Velvet upper",
        "tab_4": "Microfiber Napa",
        "tab_5": "Towel",
        "tab1_desc": "Cotton/polyester upper products (including the products in Borregatas, Espadrilles, Mules Essential, Moc Essential, Sandal Straps, Sandal Crossed, Mary Janes Raw).",
        "tab2_desc": "Synthetic Suede upper products (Clogs Vegan Suede, Sandal Straps, Moc Vegan Suede)\n\nCleaning synthetic suede requires a delicate touch, but it can be done effectively with the right approach. Here are the steps you can follow to clean synthetic suede:",
        "tab3_desc": "Velvet upper products (selected products Mary Janes Gum)\n\nVelvet shoes require a bit of a gentler care when it comes to cleaning, but with the right approach, it's possible to keep them looking great for a long time.",
        "tab4_desc": "Microfiber Napa upper products (Loafer Microfiber Napa, Mary Janes Microfiber Napa, Tulipa Microfiber Napa, Moc Microfiber Napa, Mule Microfiber Napa) requires specific easy-to-do steps, to ensure their durability. Follow these steps and they’ll last for a long time.",
        "tab5_desc": "Towel upper products (including the products in Mocs).",
        "tab1_footer": "<br>For outstanding cleaning, please pay particular attention to the following:<br>\n                    You can stuff your Paez with some kitchen paper or a dry cloth to help them keep their shape as they dry.\n                    <br><br>Heads up! If your Paez have yute (or rope) soles, take extra care and avoid squeezing them with excess water. Instead, gently wipe them down with a damp cloth.\n                    <br><br>Just a friendly reminder: Whatever you do, don't put your Paez in the washing machine or dryer. That's a big no-no.\n                    <br><br>As for the soles, you can simply wipe them clean with a damp cloth. And if you're wondering about the insoles, they're non-removable and vegan. Keep them fresh by giving your shoes a chance to breathe or using an insole spray.",
        "tab2_footer": "<br>For outstanding cleaning, please pay particular attention to the following:<br>\n                    You can stuff your Paez with some kitchen paper or a dry cloth to help them keep their shape as they dry.\n                    <br><br>Heads up! If your Paez have yute (or rope) soles, take extra care and avoid squeezing them with excess water. \n                    <br><br>Instead, gently wipe them down with a damp cloth.\n                    <br><br>Just a friendly reminder: Whatever you do, don't put your Paez in the washing machine or dryer. That's a big no-no.\n                    <br><br>As for the soles, you can simply wipe them clean with a damp cloth. And if you're wondering about the insoles, they're non-removable and vegan.",
        "tab3_footer": "<br>Tip if you're a pro: To restore the nap of the velvet and keep it looking soft and fluffy, use a steamer or hold the shoes over a pot of boiling water for a few seconds. Be careful though not to get the shoes too close to the steam or water, as this can damage the velvet.\n                    <br><br>Tip if you're not a pro: take it to a professional cleaner who can assure your shoes last as much time as you wish for :)\n                    <br><br>Just a friendly reminder: Whatever you do, don't put your Paez in the washing machine or dryer. That's a big no-no.\n                    <br><br>As for the soles, you can simply wipe them clean with a damp cloth. And if you're wondering about the insoles, they're non-removable and vegan. Keep them fresh by giving your shoes a chance to breathe or using an insole spray.",
        "tab4_footer": "For outstanding cleaning, please pay attention to the following:<br>\nTo keep vegan leather supple and prevent it from drying out and cracking, consider applying a specialized vegan leather conditioner. Follow the manufacturer's instructions for application carefully.<br><br>\n\nStore properly and protect the shoes from moisture: When not in use, store your vegan leather shoes in a cool, dry place away from direct sunlight. Avoid storing them in plastic bags or airtight containers, as this can trap moisture and lead to mold or mildew growth.",
        "tab5_footer": "For outstanding cleaning, please pay particular attention to the following:\nTo dry, place your shoes in a cool, dry spot, away from any direct sunlight or heat waves. Heat can cause the fabric to stiff.<br><br>\n\nStuffing is especially important for this material to retain shape. You can do it with kitchen paper or a clean cloth while they dry.<br><br>\n\nProduct with yute soles, need an extra step: avoid soaking them in water—just wipe the sole with a slightly damp cloth to avoid damaging the fibers.<br><br>\n\nJust a friendly reminder: Whatever you do, don't put your Paez in the washing machine or dryer. That's a big no-no.<br><br>\n\nAs for the soles, you can simply wipe them clean with a damp cloth. And if you're wondering about the insoles, they're non-removable and vegan. Keep them fresh by giving your shoes a chance to breathe or using an insole spray."
      }
    },
    "e6fa25ec-2dd8-4166-aea3-528f33827c7e": {
